<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>insensitive about something • insensitive to something</xh5><p> <i>insensitive about something—</i>not easily offended or worried about smth.: Ping mentally berated herself for being so absolutely <u>insensitive about</u> the cleanliness of his house.</p><p> <i>insensitive to something—</i>1. not susceptible or vulnerable to smth.: The virus is highly <u>insensitive to</u> cold, which renders it capable of surviving during prolonged periods of sub-freezing temperatures. 2. unable to understanding other people’s feelings, hardships, etc.: We put blinders on our ability to see the needs of others. We become <u>insensitive to</u> their problems, to their suffering, to their poverty.</p> </entry>
